Information secure shredder for in memory or backing store information Objects
Secure, permanent destruction of information in memory on backing storage is problematic in modern operating systems, because they are largely ineffective.
SSDs do not overwrite data in place. When a shredder tells an SSD to overwrite a file, the drive’s firmware often writes the new data to a completely different location to manage wear, leaving the original "sensitive" data intact until garbage collection cleans it up later.

